{
  "doc_id": "49507",
  "text": "The potential use of acute phase proteins as indicators of general health and the effects of stress on cattle has been investigated by many researchers. [CITATION_1] investigated the concentrations of APPs in relation to health status, and found that calves with a higher incidence of diseases had more days on which they exhibited elevated concentrations of acute phase proteins suggesting that APPs could be a useful tool for evaluation of health status in calves. [CITATION_2] described an increase in acute phase proteins in response to stress stimuli in calves. [CITATION_3] reported that in calves, stress caused by housing on a slippery floor had no effect on the concentrations of Hp, but that the concentrations of SAA increased.",
